						<summary>

						<p>The king is called Parakēsarivarman “who took Madirai and Īḻam”. This is also damaged and perhaps also engraved by an ignorant scribe. It registers an endowment of 2000 <hi rend="italic">kuḻi</hi> of land after purchase by Dēvaṉ Gōvindaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Pirānta[ka*] Anukki Śōḻanāyakaṉ of Pūḷikuḍi (?) in Śēṟṟūr-kūṟṟam for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple at Gōvindapāḍi in Valla-nāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
